 {"id":"franken_networkx-qoi1","title":"parity: DegreeView should be callable like NetworkX","description":"In NetworkX, G.degree, G.in_degree, and G.out_degree return views that are callable: G.degree() returns the view, G.degree('a') returns int degree of node a, G.degree(['a','b']) returns filtered view. FrankenNetworkX's degree views are not callable - calling G.degree() raises TypeError. This affects Graph.degree, DiGraph.degree/in_degree/out_degree, and similar MultiGraph variants.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-21T11:52:50.294011693Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T12:01:05.709076048Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T12:01:05.707032718Z","close_reason":"Fixed: Added __call__ to DegreeView and DiDegreeView. Commit 15aae11.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-qoz2","title":"parity: to_directed live views should support in_edges and out_edges","description":"The top-level to_directed() live views currently lack in_edges() and out_edges() entirely, for both Graph and MultiGraph inputs. NetworkX exposes these directed edge iterators on the resulting DiGraph/MultiDiGraph view, including keyed variants for multigraphs. Match the upstream directed edge-iterator surface instead of returning a view with missing methods.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T07:14:14.023226100Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T07:15:15.749473056Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
